annotations: Re-up on the riz, little snacks, the fizzy pop

‘Riz’ refers to Rizla rolling papers used for rolling cigarettes. La Rue isn’t shy about discussing their smoking habit, even admitting that she met her fellow Nine8 Collective members “in the smoking area” after “a teacher failed to show up for class” while they were attending Kingston college.

Listen to SZA while we eating
 Like hickory, dickory, dock
 How many times can ya finish round the clock?

SZA is a popular R&B artist and it’s likely that La Rue is referencing her song “Broken Clocks” with the multiple references to clocks in these lines.

While SZA hasn’t confirmed her sexuality, she was recently rumoured to be dating fellow singer Kehlani after photos emerged of the two getting close. This could perhaps be why La Rue chose to reference her in particular.



The final line likely refers to La Rue’s ability to give her partner multiple orgasms.
But I can be the Rue to your Jules

Rue and Jules are characters from the HBO TV show ‘Euphoria’, played by Zendaya and Hunter Schafer respectively. Throughout the show, the two teenage girls engage in a complicated, fast paced relationship that has been very popular with fans.



La Rue is telling her partner that she could give her the same intense kind of love, though hopefully their relationship would be slightly less messy.
In my vest and boxers

In an interview with Line of Best Fit, La Rue describes how this choice in clothing implies their sexuality:

“Vest & Boxers” is what we would refer to as our ‘dyke uniform’ – we’d wear it under our baggy denim/oversized suits with the waist band showing as a little signal to all the other gays in the room.

description.plain:
“G.O.Y.D.” marks the first collaboration between Lava La Rue and Clairo. It features the production of Lava La Rue, Joe Thornalley, Aiwa Laurel, Claire Cottrill, Joe Thornalley and Dan Holloway. The single was released on 11 September 2020.

The title is a reference to Clairo’s previous song “B.O.M.D.” or “Boy of My Dreams”. “G.O.Y.D.” or “Girl of Your Dream” is Lava La Rue’s answer to Clairo’s song.

annotations:
Bleming spirit just to keep all my lungs warm
 I been living off my winnings so fast though, ah
“Blem” is a UK slang word for a roll up cigarette and spirit referring to American spirit (tobacco) I am spending all of my winnings (income) on heating my lungs with a past nicotine addiction.
I’ll see you in my REM state

In sleep, REM or Rapid Eye Movement sleep is associated with dreaming, memory consolidation, learning, and problem solving. During REM sleep, you can expect high brain activity, where your brain interprets neurons firing as your dreams. The body becomes immobile to stop you from acting out dreams.

Clairo accepts that she may only be able to see the other person in her dreams.
But I can’t lie, baby Benz, I think I like you
Baby benz is Claire’s DJ’s name although “she doesn’t know shit about cars”
Molly ’cause I been rolling like a heartthrob
Lava is comparing the feeling MDMA brings to a heartthrob which is a man, typically a celebrity, whose good looks excite immature romantic feelings in women. She says she has as much success as them
